@startuml

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE

skinparam activity {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    ArrowColor #495057
    FontColor #212529
    DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF3CD
    DiamondBorderColor #856404
    StartColor #28A745
    EndColor #DC3545
    BarColor #495057
}

skinparam swimlane {
    BorderColor #6C757D
    TitleFontColor #212529
    TitleBackgroundColor #E9ECEF
}

skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #E7F3FE
    BorderColor #3D9AD1
    FontColor #212529
}

title Single Agent Turn Execution\n<size:11>run_single_turn() — run_loop.py | One complete agent turn: prompt → model → response → next step</size>

|Runner|
start
:run_single_turn(\nbindings, all_tools, original_input,\ngenerated_items, hooks, context_wrapper, run_config);

:Convert original_input → turn_input list\nItemHelpers.input_to_new_input_list();

if (should_run_agent_start_hooks?) then (yes)
    :Fire **on_agent_start()**\n[RunHooks + AgentHooks in parallel];
endif

fork
    :get_system_prompt(context_wrapper);
fork again
    :get_prompt(context_wrapper);
end fork

:Resolve output_schema\nget_output_schema(execution_agent);

:Resolve enabled handoffs\nget_handoffs(execution_agent, context_wrapper);
note right
  Each Handoff checked:
  is_enabled (bool or callable)
  evaluated at runtime
end note

:Prepare turn input items\n_prepare_turn_input_items(\noriginal_input, generated_items,\nreasoning_item_id_policy)\nor server_conversation_tracker.prepare_input();

|Model Layer|
note right : **get_new_response()**

:Apply optional input filter\nmaybe_filter_model_input() → ModelInputData;
note right
  RunConfig.call_model_input_filter
  transforms input before sending
  to the model (optional)
end note

:Deduplicate input items;

:Resolve model & model_settings\nmaybe_reset_tool_choice if\ntool_use_tracker indicates needed;

:Fire **on_llm_start()**\n[RunHooks + AgentHooks in parallel];

repeat
    :model.get_response(\nsystem_instructions, input,\nmodel_settings, tools,\noutput_schema, handoffs)\nvia get_response_with_retry();
repeat while (Retry required?) is (yes — rewind_session_items()\n+ server_conversation_tracker.rewind_input())
->no;

:Accumulate usage\ncontext_wrapper.usage.add(response.usage);

:Fire **on_llm_end()**\n[RunHooks + AgentHooks in parallel];

:Return **ModelResponse**(output, usage, response_id);

|Turn Resolution|
note right : **process_model_response()** — turn_resolution.py

:Iterate response.output items\nClassify each item by type;

fork
    :message_output\n→ MessageOutputItem\n\nreasoning\n→ ReasoningItem;
fork again
    :function_call (handoff name match)\n→ ToolRunHandoff\n\nfunction_call (tool name match)\n→ ToolRunFunction;
fork again
    :computer_use_call\n→ ToolRunComputerAction\n\nshell_call → ToolRunShellCall\nlocal_shell_call → ToolRunLocalShellCall\napply_patch_call → ToolRunApplyPatchCall;
fork again
    :mcp_call / mcp_list_tools /\nmcp_approval_request\n→ MCP items\n\nfile_search / web_search /\ncode_interpreter / image_generation\n→ hosted tool items (no local exec);
end fork

:Return **ProcessedResponse**\n(new_items, handoffs, functions,\ncomputer_actions, local_shell_calls,\nshell_calls, mcp_approval_requests,\ninterruptions, custom_tool_calls, tools_used);

:tool_use_tracker.record_processed_response();

note right : **execute_tools_and_side_effects()** — turn_resolution.py

:Build tool execution plan\n_build_plan_for_fresh_turn(\nprocessed_response, agent,\ncontext_wrapper, approval_items_by_call_id);

:Deduplicate tool call items\n_dedupe_tool_call_items() → new_step_items;

|Tool Execution|

:Execute tool plan\n_execute_tool_plan(\nplan, bindings, hooks, context_wrapper, run_config);
note right
  Per FunctionTool:
  ① Fire on_tool_start() [RunHooks + AgentHooks]
  ② Apply tool_input_guardrail (if configured)
  ③ Execute tool asynchronously
  ④ Apply tool_output_guardrail (if configured)
  ⑤ Fire on_tool_end() [RunHooks + AgentHooks]
  Also executes: computer_results, shell_results,
  apply_patch_results, local_shell_results
end note

:Build tool result items\n_build_tool_result_items()\nappend results to new_step_items;

:Collect tool interruptions\n_collect_tool_interruptions()\nfrom function / shell / apply_patch results;

:Append approved MCP callback results\n_append_mcp_callback_results();

|Turn Resolution|

if (Interruptions present?) then (yes)
    :Return **SingleStepResult**\nnext_step = **NextStepInterruption**\n(interruptions: list[ToolApprovalItem]);
    note right
      Human-in-the-loop approval required.
      Run is paused; resumption goes through
      resolve_interrupted_turn()
    end note
    stop
endif

if (Handoffs in ProcessedResponse?) then (yes)
    :execute_handoffs()\n→ apply handoff.input_filter (if set)\n→ nest_handoff_history (if configured);
    :Fire **on_handoff()**\n[RunHooks + AgentHooks in parallel];
    :Return **SingleStepResult**\nnext_step = **NextStepHandoff**(new_agent);
    note right
      Handoffs are exposed as tools to the LLM:
      transfer_to_<agent_name>
      New agent takes over in next loop iteration
    end note
    stop
endif

if (tool_use_behavior produces final output?) then (yes)
    note right
      'stop_on_first_tool'   → use first tool result
      {stop_at_tool_names}   → match by tool name
      callable behavior      → is_final_output == True
      Default: 'run_llm_again' (tool results feed back into loop)
    end note
    :Extract final output\nfrom matching tool result;
    :Fire **on_agent_end()**\n[RunHooks + AgentHooks in parallel];
    :Return **SingleStepResult**\nnext_step = **NextStepFinalOutput**(output);
    stop
endif

if (has_tools_or_approvals_to_run()?) then (yes)
    :Return **SingleStepResult**\nnext_step = **NextStepRunAgain**\n(tool results appended to input);
    note right
      Runner loop re-enters run_single_turn()
      with accumulated tool results.
      Continues until max_turns exceeded.
    end note
    stop
endif

note right : No pending tools — produce final answer

if (output_schema is structured JSON?) then (yes)
    :Validate JSON response\noutput_schema.validate_json();
    note right
      AgentOutputSchema validates the
      model's structured output before
      returning as final
    end note
endif

:Fire **on_agent_end()**\n[RunHooks + AgentHooks in parallel];

:Return **SingleStepResult**\nnext_step = **NextStepFinalOutput**(output);

stop

@enduml
